        <p>
            <h2>What is Care Architecture?</h2>
Care Architecture is developing Care Neighborhood, a national social-networking and e-commerce platform that will be implemented and experienced at the level of local communities. Care Neighborhood will provide social connectedness and access to services for the elderly and disabled to enable them to remain independent in their home environments â€“ and peace of mind to their families. Care Architecture aims to develop partnerships with community-based organizations ranging along a continuum from health to social to aging services.
        </p>
        <p>
There are currently 42 million Americans over the age of 65 and 12 million non-elderly disabled. Ten thousand Boomers will turn 65 each day between now and 2029.
        </p>
        <p>
Care Neighborhood is designed to meet the evolving needs of seniors as the concept of seniorhood changes, and the population of seniors grows. The concept of retirement is changing, and younger seniors are staying in the workforce beyond the traditional retirement age of 65. They need improved access to employment and volunteer opportunities. Older seniors and the disabled need quality home- and community-based services.
        </p>
        <p>
